I'm giving a talk on JUnit next month at the Lone Star Software
Symposium in Dallas, TX.  Giddy-up!

The presentation is a technical primer to using JUnit and the techniques
of test-first design.  It also covers examples uses of Ant, Cactus,
HttpUnit, and JUnitPerf, among others.

If anyone in the Dallas area is interested, email me privately for
details.  It would be great to meet some folks on this list.

Thanks,
